package Method;

public class Methods_in_java {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
//        Objects --> Has-part(state/properties) and Does-part(fields/variables)
// 1--> a method is like a function, aia s block of code or collection of statements grouped together to perform a certain
//        or operation.Rhe differences is that a method is associated with an object, while a function is not.
//        2--> In  java,methods arw used to implement the behavior of the object.
//        3--> A method must always be declared within a class.
//        4--> A method can directly access all the instance variables  of the enclosing class.

//        syntax of Method
//        modifiers return_type method_name(parameter)exception_list
//        {
//            // body of the method
//        }

//        Method declarations have six components, in order:
//  1-->Modifiers--->
//  2-->The return type-->
//  3-->The method name-->
//  4-->The parameter list in parenthesis -->
//   5--> An exception list -->
//  6-->The method body, enclosed betwwen braces-->
    }
